parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Light Lead Contact Point Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The melting of the lead contact points for the brake lights can cause the brake lights to malfunction, which can lead to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: The brake lights do not work
the lead contact points are melted
the tail fin brake light still works
but the actual brake lights do not.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine misfire and stalling issue can cause the vehicle to lose power and stall, which can lead to accidents, especially when driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: the issue occurs when the car gets wet
the vehicle has been in the shop multiple times for the same problem.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The insufficient illumination from the low beam headlights can lead to reduced visibility, increased eye strain, and potentially cause accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: Low beam headlights are too dim
do not illuminate the road sufficiently
forcing drivers to use high beams
high beams shine like low beams should
and require eye strain at highway speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected deployment of airbags can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if it occurs while the vehicle is in motion. It can also lead to unnecessary repair costs and downtime.
symptoms: airbags deploy without any apparent reason.
